replies.body:
Frozen Heart isn't unappealing because it doesn't have health, it's the oversaturation of CDR.

For example, all MR tank items have CDR. All of them. {{item:3001}} {{item:3065}} {{item:3194}} 

All tanky-Support items have CDR. {{item:3109}} {{item:3050}} {{item:3800}} 

Finally, a lot of Fighter items have CDR. {{item:3071}} {{item:3078}} {{item:3812}} 

And also Warmogs has CDR. {{item:3083}} 

Most Tank items without CDR also don't have Health. {{item:3193}} {{item:3190}} 

Frozen Heart was a good item because it provided a LOT of Armor, a lot of Mana, and a lot of CDR. Now that one of it's special niches is gone, it's underwhelming as a whole.

Combine that with the fact that other Armor based items don't have CDR, and Frozen Heart is even less attractive over those options. You get all the CDR you need from the MR/Supp items. {{item:3075}} {{item:3143}} {{item:3742}} {{item:3068}} 

Frozen Heart doesn't need any more buffing (The 10 Armor was warranted a long time ago), CDR needs to be reduced across the board.

Personally, I'd take CDR out of Warmogs, Adaptive Helm, and Righteous Glory.
